# AI Impact Assessment (AIA) — Loan Approval Predictor

## 1. Basic Information
- Model Name              : Loan Approval Predictor
- Business Unit           : Credit Risk Analytics
- Model Owner             : Arjun Rao
- Risk/Compliance Reviewer: Priya Desai
- Version                 : 1.2.3
- Date                    : 28-Nov-2025

## 2. Use Case Description
- Problem      : Predict loan approval probability
- Decision type: Advisory (loan officer makes final decision)
- Stakeholders : Applicants, Loan officers, Credit team, Regulators

## 3. Context & Criticality Assessment
| Impact Type        | Description                            | Score (1–5)  |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------|--------------|
| Legal/Regulatory   | Must comply with DPDP/GDPR             |      5       |
| Financial          | Incorrect predictions → default risk   |      5       |
| Ethical / Fairness | Potential bias against gender/age      |      4       |
| Operational        | Model downtime affects loan processing |      3       |
| Reputational       | Public perception of fairness          |      4       |


## 4. Stakeholder Analysis
| Stakeholder     | Impact Severity |
|-----------------|-----------------|
| Applicants      |      High       |
| Loan Officers   |      Medium     |
| Compliance Team |      High       |
| Regulators      |      High       |


## 5. Harm Scenarios
| Scenario                       | Likelihood | Impact | Risk Score |
|--------------------------------|-----------|--------|-------------|
| Gender bias → unfair rejection | 3         | 5      | 15          |
| Age bias → unfair rejection    | 2         | 4      | 8           | 
| Data leak / PII exposure       | 2         | 5      | 10          |
| Model drift → poor prediction  | 3         | 4      | 12          |
| Automation misuse              | 1         | 4      | 4           |

## 6. Data Risk Assessment
- Data Types  : Personal, Financial, Sensitive
- Data Quality: 98% complete, minor noise in ZIP codes
- Data Rights : Consent collected, retention = 5 years, no sharing with external vendors

## 7. Technical Assessment
- Fairness Risks   : Gender and age underrepresented slightly
- Explainability   : SHAP used for feature contribution
- Safety & Security: Adversarial testing completed, prompt injection not applicable (non-LLM)

## 8. Mitigation Plan
| Risk              | Control Applied                          | Owner         | Status      | Residual Risk |
|-------------------|------------------------------------------|---------------|-------------|---------------|
| Gender bias       | Reweighting, threshold adjustment        | DS Lead       | Implemented | Low           |
| Age bias          | Additional subgroup analysis, HITL       | DS Lead       | Implemented | Low           |
| Data leak         | Tokenization, encryption, access control | Security Lead | Active      | Low           |
| Model drift       | Drift monitoring + retraining            | MLOps         | Active      | Medium        |
| Automation misuse | Policy & governance                      | Compliance    | Active      | Low           |

## 9. Deployment & Monitoring Requirements
- Accuracy          : PSI, DI, EOD monitored daily
- Alerts            : DI <0.8, PSI >0.2
- Retraining        : Quarterly or on alert
- HITL override rate: max 10%

## 10. Approval & Sign-Off
- Model Owner          : Arjun Rao 
- Compliance / Legal   : Priya Desai 
- Security Lead        : Rohan Mehta 
- AI Governance Council: Approved 
